   "Dig In!" Hands-On Soil Investigations

   The National Science Teachers Association (NSTA) and the Natural
   Resources Conservation Service announce the release of "Dig In!"
   Hands-On Soil Investigations.

   This lively, 129-page softbound book is a bestseller assisting
   educators across the nation in teaching scientifically accurate soil
   and soil conservation information in an enjoyable way. The book is
   available from NSTA by calling or writing.

          National Science Teachers Association
          1840 Wilson Boulevard
          Arlington, VA 22201-3000

   or call 703-243-7100 or 1-800-277-5300 ; or visit the NSTA Book Store
   online.

   For other soil information visit:
   http://www.statlab.iastate.edu/soils/soildiv/

